Premium Till when will we sleep? Are we waiting for the day they capture our homes? Verified Orgs This map highlights the alarming demographic shift taking place in Bengal Profile The marked constituencies are those where the voter population increased by more than 40 percent between 2011 and 2021. This is not a random trend. It is a well planned and systematic transformation carried More out under political patronage. The dream of turning Bengal into an Islamic state, once crushed by forefathers like Shyama Prasad Mookerjee Ji and warriors like Gopal Patha, Post still lives on. And this time, Mamata is enabling it with her support. In 46 assembly constituencies, the voter population has increased by more than 40 percent within just a decade. In 7 of them, the increase is over 50 percent. That means nearly half the current electorate is new. And we have not even considered the changes that happened after 2021 or before 2011. Apart from these, there are 118 assembly constituencies where voter growth is between 30% and 40% percent. Among these 46 seats 10 are from Malda 10 from South 24 Parganas 9 from Murshidabad 7 from Uttar Dinajpur 4 from Dakshin Dinajpur 2 from North 24 Parganas 2 from Jalpaiguri 2 from Darjeeling This is not natural growth. This is demographic engineering. This is an invasion. And all of it is happening under Mamata’s watch. Why does Mohammad Yunus dare to speak about the Chicken’s Neck? Because he knows that the demography of that region is being changed and he has full support from Mamata. That is why his new ambassador rushed to meet her. Mamata knows these are her voters. That is why she cries and shouts for them. That is why she fears voter list sanitization. Because without Bangladeshi Muslim votes, she cannot even touch 30 percent vote share. Speaking Bangla does not mean being Bengali If we do not raise our voices now, we will soon be outnumbered in our own homeland. Bengal is not just losing its culture. It is losing its identity, its land, and Prathamesh Anand everything it once stood for. @Prathamesh56451 The choice is simple. You either stand with Bengal or you stand against it. There is no middle ground. History will remember those who betrayed their motherland for money and votes. Home We appeal to all Hindus. Set aside your party lines and stand for your state.
